						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab in the Museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vikramāditya VI (Date lost).</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers itself to the reign of <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva,</hi> ruling from the capital <hi rend="bold">Jayantīpura.</hi> Only the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> of the king is preserved. On paleographic grounds the record would appear to be of the time of Vikramāditya VI. </p>						

						</summary>
